==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rightfulness
<hw>Right"ful*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or
state of being rightful; accordance with right and justice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Moral rectitude; righteousness.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Wyclif.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We fail of perfect <qex>rightfulness</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir P.
Sidney.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Right-hand</ent>⟦br⟧
